title: US and Denmark discuss Greenland 'military access' in more conventional talks
subhed: Talks have begun between Denmark and the United States over a deal addressing American ambitions in Greenland. Calling for indefinite 'total access' to the island, Donald Trump seems to be seeking to establish new military bases there.

title: Defiant protests over US immigration crackdown, child's detention
subhed: Thousands of Minnesotans braved subzero temperatures to protest the Trump administration's immigration crackdown, with dozens of businesses and restaurants shuttering their doors in solidarity.

title: 'We were walking in blood': Iran's doctors recount crackdown on protesters
subhed: From crowded emergency rooms to apocalyptic scenes in Iranian cities, healthcare workers told Le Monde about the violence that descended on protesters calling for the end of the Iranian regime from January 8.

title: Paris police Louvre warned about security risks six weeks before heist
subhed: In a report sent to the Louvre's management several weeks before the October 19 heist, the Police Prefecture described 'all of the resources dedicated to security as outdated and unsuitable for the site.'

title: Generative AI, psychiatry and the risks of self-service therapy
subhed: Millions of people use chatbots like ChatGPT to share their distress, and the scientific community has warned about the risks vulnerable people face. Generative AI has shaken up psychiatric consultations, fueled tech giants' ambitions and emerged as a credible tool for analyzing pathologies.

subhed: Like other European nationalists, Marine Le Pen has been put in a tough spot by Donald Trump's imperialist offensive. But the MAGA ideological campaign in Europe, of which France is a key target, has won over her Rassemblement National party over the past year.

title: 'As it ceases to inspire, the US is losing part of itself'
subhed: Donald Trump's second term has turned the United States into a threat to which the rest of the world has no choice but to adapt. Yet, over the past eight decades, habits and practices have taken root that will be used to counter this new imperialism, writes Le Monde columnist Gilles Paris.

title: An era of distrust emerges between the US and its Western allies
subhed: Donald Trump's suggestion that the US could seize Greenland by force has exposed the strategic isolation his administration has chosen, in disregard for the country's commitments. Even though the Republican president abandoned the idea at Davos, the damage to US credibility is substantial.
